The paper focuses on analyzing individual neurons in deep neural networks for natural language processing tasks, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses methods for extracting relevant neurons and evaluating their importance for specific tasks, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of vector representations, which is a common technique in neural networks for computer vision (cs.CV) and neural engineering (cs.NE).
